\begin_layout Subsection
RESTful APIs calls
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The first solution we came up with, is to create a single batch job that
 consumes a RESTful API for each step, where we can call for the reading,
 processing and writing operations.
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
However, this solution mandates that the client expose these RESTful APIs,
 and host it somewhere on his own servers, we cannot guarantee that all
 our clients would be able to host a RESTful APIs.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Another drawback is that this solution would be very inefficient, we would
 bombard the client servers by our calls, and the processing would be done
 on their servers as-well.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
This solution is quite simple but presents lots of inefficiencies.
\end_layout

